@node start "The start"

           (¯`·._.·' Mr Convert `·._.·'¯)


             (_.·'¯`· The start ·'¯`·._)

    These are the CLI/WB arguments:

    @{fg shine}DESTINATION@{fg text}=directory

        The destination directory.
        Where the converted files will be placed.

    @{fg shine}SOURCE@{fg text}=directory

        The source directory.
        When you hit the "Add" gadget, this is the dir
        the browser will show.

    @{fg shine}SCREEN@{fg text}=name

        The pubscreen name of the desired screen.
        If not found, Workbench will be used.

    @{fg shine}PC2AM@{fg text}=directory

        By default the convertation way is
        Amiga to PC, this will make it PC to Amiga.

    @{fg shine}FONTNAME@{fg text}=name.font

        The name of the font you wish to use

    @{fg shine}FONTSIZE@{fg text}=size

        The size of the font you wish to use

    @{fg shine}OVERWRITE@{fg text}

        Default setting is to ask the user to confirm
        overwriting a file. With this argument the
        program will owerwrite files without asking.

    @{fg shine}LIST@{fg text}=file

        Load a @{" filelist " link filelist} during startup.

    @{fg shine}IFLISTGOQUIT@{fg text}

        If you use the LIST argument, this argument can
        be used as well.
            Then MrConvert will start, load the @{" filelist " link filelist},
            convert the files and quit.

        Voila! :)

    @{fg shine}SHOWLIST@{fg text}=mode

        This changes the way the filenames are shown in
        the listview.

        mode can be:

            NAME (default)
                View the filename without path

            PATH
                View the whole path

            RIGHT
                Supposed to show the right part of the filename...
                Doesn't work correctly with every font.


@endnode
@node window "The window"

           (¯`·._.·' Mr Convert `·._.·'¯)


            (_.·'¯`· The window ·'¯`·._)


          Convert files:
        +----------------+
        |                |
        |                |
        |  @{" file list " link filelist}  |
        |                |
        |                |
        |                |
        +----------------+

Add               - To add file(s) to the file list

Remove            - Remove selected file from file list

Clear             - Clear the file list

Yes, overwrite    - Do not ask for users confirmation to overwrite files

Destination       - Press the gadget and a pathrequester will ask
                    you for the destination of the converted files.
                    This can NOT be in the same drawer as the source file(s).

Convertation way  - Do you want to convert Amiga files to PC files or vice versa?

So, let's convert - Convert the files!

Converting:
    The upper text-field contains the name of the file being converted.
    The lower contains the name of the next file to be converted,
    and number of files left.

    The small box, to the right of the lower field,
    shines with pen 3 (blue) and gray (0) while converting a file,
    pen 2 (white) when a file is converted.

@endnode


@node filelist "File list"

           (¯`·._.·' Mr Convert `·._.·'¯)


             (_.·'¯`· Filelist ·'¯`·._)


In the main window, there is a listview.
This listview contains the files that
are loaded to be converted.

The filelist's filenames can be shown
in three different ways.
    Check the @{" startup arguments " link start}


You can save and load lists like this on disk,
from the "file list" menu.
    Save it and load it later to easily convert
the same files again.

Also look at the @{" IFLISTGOQUIT argument " link start}

@endnode
